# Build the Schedule (bus side)

## Question

The clock half, in joelclaw: a versioned event contract
(`pane/schedule.requested`: verb wake|spawn|revive, at (ISO) or in
(duration), target (pane/agent for wake), briefPath (spawn), loopId
(revive), prompt, requestedBy, scheduleId), an inngest function that
validates, `step.sleepUntil(at)`, then emits the **due signal** to the
gateway (`pane.schedule.due` with the full entry + late flag when fired
past T by more than the runner's natural slop), and `joelclaw wake`
(subcommands: at/in/list/cancel — list and cancel ride inngest's run
APIs or a small registry the function maintains). HATEOAS envelopes,
Effect idioms, tests per repo checklist. The dispatcher's execution of
the due signal is its own question.

## Answer (2026-07-14)

Built the versioned `pane/schedule.requested` contract, the host-side
`pane/schedule` Inngest function, Redis-backed pending registry, cancellation
via `pane/schedule.cancelled`, and `joelclaw wake at|in|list|cancel`. The
function sleeps with `step.sleepUntil(at)` and emits `pane.schedule.due` with
the full schedule entry, `firedAt`, and a `late` flag after five minutes.
Dispatcher execution remains out of scope.

